what is your favorite sea creature what kind and why do you like it bottle nose dolphin they're so curious and seeing several hundred leaping out of waves and playing at the bow at sea is unforgettable and then there's little or fairy penguins brave little fellers you'll find many miles from shore in mobs fishing deep in defiance of sharks and often chirruping around a boat in protest at night you'll hear them when sailing not when motoring not forgetting albert ross the albatross soaring gracefully across the faces of waves in heavy weather caring nothing for the storm or the land or the streams of mutton birds like strewn black roses on the sea as they fish and like aerial rivers of bats as they home to their burrows ashore at sunset for their community and even the squabbling seagulls of the shore like the re incarnations of dead sailors clinging to the sea and fighting for scraps like alcoholics their uniforms so clean on the outside and often so lice infested underneath for their defiant courage and determination to survive even after a barracuda or shark has taken a leg or two i miss them all here far ashore where only the dark clouds of bad weather come to remind me of more alarming and wonderful days USS Wadsworth (DD-516) Seabird USS Wichita (CA-45) Ecco the Dolphin USS Tunny (SS-282) Fauna of Australia Glossary of nautical terms USS Wasp (CV-18) Ecology of Hong Kong USS Wickes (DD-578) USS West Virginia (BB-48) Link (Legend of Zelda) Navigation USS Whale (SS-239) USS Zane (DD-337) Albatross USS Thresher (SS-200) Dolphin Treehouse of Horror XI Finding Nemo United States Coast Guard One Piece minor characters Anchor USS Harder (SS-257) Weather lore USS Ticonderoga (CV-14) Shark USS Uhlmann (DD-687) Gliding Dinghy Lou Gehrig USS Albatross (1861) Joe DiMaggio Gal__pagos Islands USS Waters (DD-115) USS Sea Devil (SS-400) Bocas del Toro Province Submarine The Old Man and the Sea USS Vincennes (CL-64) Babe Ruth USS Ammen (DD-527) Creatures in Bionicle USS Thompso